description: Metropolis is under mystical siege, trapping Emil inside S.T.A.R. Labs with an unlikely source of help.

The streets of New York run red with criminal blood, as the families of organized crime wage war on each other. The streets of London conceal an international conspiracy that may very well put an end to humanity. And Lamont Cranston, aka The Shadow, has retired. WTF!?!!

description: Asterix stories 19, 20, and 21, together in one fabulous volume! In Asterix and the Soothsayer, the sinister Prolix claims he's clairvoyant - but Asterix isn't convinced. Asterix in Corsica has Asterix and Obelix out to foil Praetor Perfidius and oppose Caesar's army. Legionary Tremensdelirius gets the deed to the Gaulish village in Caesar's Gift; but Asterix isn't about to hand over his home!
name: Vol. 7

description: The path of true love never did run smooth - especially when the sweethearts' fathers have split their town in half. That's the problem for Histrionix and the beautiful Melodrama in Asterix and the Great Divide. Asterix and Obelix face a dangerous double agent in Asterix and the Black Gold. And it's two Gauls and a baby when Asterix and Obelix tare of an abandoned infant - and try to keep it out of Roman hands - in Asterix and Son.
name: Vol. 9

name: RIn Tin Tin en de Wapen  Smokkelaars

description: Discover how Denny Colt becomes the masked vigilante known as the Spirit!
name: The Origin of The Spirit

description: It's a modern day case of Macbeth and Lady Macbeth between the sniveling Snipe and his wife Goldie, who pushes her husband to act more like a "man."
name: Women!

description: In the year 2941, archeologists unearth a comic book tale of the Spirit story dealing with the Oldest Man in the World.
name: The Oldest Man in the World

description: Hop aboard a $100,000 ride into mystery, but for the Spirit, it could be a one-way trip!
name: The Last Trolley

description: Featuring the first appearance of the villainous Octopus.
name: The Postage Stamp

description: Featuring the first appearance of one of the Spirit's most notorious femme fatales, in this tale we meet P'Gell, a black widow who moves from husband to husband before crossing the Spirit's path.
name: Meet P’Gell

description: See the world literally through the eyes of Henry, a poor, disgruntled nobody returned from the war to a life he no longer wishes to be a part of.
name: The Killer

description: P'Gell apparently has Il Duce's locket, which contains the map to his treasure vault and half of Italy has come to America to get it back.
name: Il Duce’s Locket

description: Explore the criminal underground with beautiful and intricate imagery in a tale set in the sewers of the Spirit's hometown.
name: Life Below

description: The Spirit and readers meet Rice Wilder, a rich socialite desperate to escape her family's lifestyle.
name: Wild Rice

description: J. Rollo Dyce surrenders his fate entirely, refusing to make decisions one way or the other and instead embracing whatever the world might offer.
name: The Last Hand

description: Desperate to prove he is of value, Gerhard Schnobble heads to the top of a nearby building to take flight as he once did as a child.
name: Story of Gerhard Schnobble

description: When local truckers start losing their cargo and their lives, the Spirit investigates and discovers a modern-day siren with a voice that could kill.
name: Lorelei Rox

description: Quirte spends Thanksgiving in the hills, with only his bag of gold dust for company--and the ghosts.
name: Quirte

description: Two side-by-side panel-bending tales exploring the parallel lives of Carboy T. Gretch and Cranfranz Qwayle.
name: Two Lives

description: Locked away in prison on Christmas Eve, Basher Bains receives a strange means of escape from an unlikely source: a jolly man in a red suit with a sack full of presents.
name: Christmas Spirit of 1948

description: The Spirit crosses paths and wits with a woman who claims to be an invader from Mars.
name: Visitor

description: Silk Satin recruits the Spirit to help prove that her husband, Kurt, is innocent of a murder charge in the Caribbean.
name: Satin

description: Utilizing the format of children's reading primer, Eisner tells the story of how a toy machine gun winds up involved in one of the Spirit's cases.
name: Rat-Tat, the Toy Machine Gun

description: In another tale playing with the boundaries of the comic book medium we follow the final ten minutes of Freddy's life.
name: Ten Minutes

description: Autumn Mews uses her womanly wiles on Sammy to get him to spill the beans on the Spirit.
name: Death of Autumn Mews
